---
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components";
import DocLayout from "../layouts/DocLayout.astro";

const cmd = `git clone https://github.com/IEvangelist/resource-translator
cd resource-translator
npm install
npm run verify   # lint + format:check + test + build
`;
---

<DocLayout title="Contributing">
  <h1>Contributing</h1>
  <p>
    Bug reports, feature requests, and pull requests are all welcome. The action
    is small enough to be friendly to first-time contributors.
  </p>

  <h2>Local development</h2>
  <Code code={cmd} lang="bash" />

  <h2>Adding a parser</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Add a fixture under <code>__tests__/data/</code>.</li>
    <li>
      Implement <code>TranslationFileParser</code> (parse, format,
      applyTranslations, toTranslatableTextMap).
    </li>
    <li>Register it in <code>translation-file-parser-factory.ts</code>.</li>
    <li>
      Add the file extension to <code>translationFileSchemes</code> in
      <code>translation-file-finder.ts</code>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Write round-trip tests for parse → format and applyTranslations.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Coverage thresholds</h2>
  <p>
    The Jest config enforces minimum coverage. New code must keep the
    statements + lines threshold above 78% and functions above 90%. Add
    fixtures and tests alongside your change.
  </p>

  <h2>Documentation site</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>docs/</code> folder is an Astro 6 + Tailwind v4 project. Run
    <code>npm install</code> there once, then <code>npm run dev</code> for
    local preview. The <code>pages.yml</code> workflow ships docs to GitHub
    Pages on every merge.
  </p>
</DocLayout>
